----ENDF/B-VIII.0     MATERIAL 7                                     7 1451     
-----THERMAL NEUTRON SCATTERING DATA                                 7 1451     
------ENDF-6                                                         7 1451     
                                                                     7 1451     
 Temperatures = 296 400 500 600 700 800 1000 1200 deg K.             7 1451     
                                                                     7 1451     
 History                                                             7 1451     
 -------                                                             7 1451     
 this evaluation was produced at los alamos in 1993 using            7 1451     
 the same model as the ga evaluation of 1968 (ref 1).  the           7 1451     
 leapr module of njoy was used for the calculation, and              7 1451     
 the alpha and beta grids were extended slightly.  constants         7 1451     
 that match the endf/b-vi values were used.                          7 1451     
                                                                     7 1451     
 Theory                                                              7 1451     
 ------                                                              7 1451     
 the lattice dynamics of zrh were computed from a central            7 1451     
 force model.  the slightly tetragonal lattice of zrh_2 was          7 1451     
 approximated by a face-centered-cubic lattice.  four force          7 1451     
 constants (mu, gamma, nu, and delta) were introduced describing     7 1451     
 respectively the interaction of a zirconium atoms with its          7 1451     
 nearest neighbors ( 8 h atoms) and its next nearest neighbors       7 1451     
 (12 zr atoms), and the interaction of a hydrogen atom with          7 1451     
 its next nearest neighbors (6 h atoms) and its third nearest        7 1451     
 atoms (12 h atoms).  eigenvalues and eigenvectos of the             7 1451     
 dynamical matrix were calculated, and a phonon frequency            7 1451     
 spectrum was obtained by means of a root sampling technique.        7 1451     
 weighted frequency spectra for hydrogen in zrh were then            7 1451     
 obtained by appropriate use of the dynamical matrix                 7 1451     
 eigenvectors (ref. 2).                                              7 1451     
                                                                     7 1451     
 the final values of the four force constants were obtained          7 1451     
 by fitting both specific heat and neutron data.  the                7 1451     
 position of an optical peak observed by neutron scattering          7 1451     
 techniques to be centered roughly around 0.14 ev determines         7 1451     
 the constant mu, while the overall width and shape of this          7 1451     
 peak determine nu and delta respectively.  existing neutron         7 1451     
 data are not sufficiently precise to confirm the structure          7 1451     
 predicted in the optical peak by the central force model.           7 1451     
 specific heat data were used to determine the force                 7 1451     
 constant gamma, which primarily determines the upper                7 1451     
 limit on the phonon energies associated with acoustic modes.        7 1451     
                                                                     7 1451     
